    <!-- ============ Player-filter help block (collapsible) ============ -->
    <data name="ui.pntracker.filter.help.header"><value>How does filtering work?</value></data>
    <data name="ui.pntracker.filter.help.intro"><value>The player list runs every player through two stages: your active user-defined filter first, then the system filter dropdown at the top of the list. The result is the intersection of both — a player only appears when they pass every criterion of the user filter AND the visibility constraint of the system filter.</value></data>
    <data name="ui.pntracker.filter.help.system_filters.heading"><value>System filters (dropdown above the list)</value></data>
    <data name="ui.pntracker.filter.help.system_filters.body"><value>These narrow which players are even considered, independent of your user filter:</value></data>
    <data name="ui.pntracker.filter.help.system_filters.current"><value>Current players — only players currently visible in-game around you (object table, ~50 m). Empty when no one is nearby.</value></data>
    <data name="ui.pntracker.filter.help.system_filters.recent"><value>Recent players — the most recently seen N players (configurable in Tracker settings). Sorted by last-seen time.</value></data>
    <data name="ui.pntracker.filter.help.system_filters.all"><value>All players — every tracked player, no recency or visibility cap.</value></data>
    <data name="ui.pntracker.filter.help.system_filters.unread"><value>Unread history — only players with unread history changes (notifications you haven't viewed yet).</value></data>
    <data name="ui.pntracker.filter.help.user_filters.heading"><value>User-defined filters (this list)</value></data>
    <data name="ui.pntracker.filter.help.user_filters.body"><value>Each filter holds one or more criteria. All criteria within a filter are AND-joined — a player must match every single criterion to be included. An empty filter (no criteria) matches no one; the editor surfaces a placeholder hint instead. To "OR" between alternatives, build multiple filters and switch between them in the list dropdown.</value></data>
    <data name="ui.pntracker.filter.help.interaction.heading"><value>How the two stages interact</value></data>
    <data name="ui.pntracker.filter.help.interaction.body"><value>Your user filter is applied first, then the system filter trims that result. This means a user filter never expands the system filter's set — it can only further narrow it. "Recent players" + a "Free Company" criterion returns the most recent N players who also match that FC, not simply the N most recent (some of whom happen to match).</value></data>
    <data name="ui.pntracker.filter.help.example.heading"><value>A common surprise</value></data>
    <data name="ui.pntracker.filter.help.example.body"><value>You build a filter "Encountered in: Raids" and pick "Current players" — and see nothing. That's expected: the encounter criterion matches plenty of historical raid partners, but the system filter then keeps only those who happen to be on-screen right now. Switch to "All players" (or "Recent players") to see every raid partner from your encounter history.</value></data>
    <data name="ui.pntracker.filter.help.troubleshoot.heading"><value>Filter shows nothing — what to check</value></data>
    <data name="ui.pntracker.filter.help.troubleshoot.body"><value>1. Switch the system filter to "All players" — if matches appear, your system filter was the culprit. 2. Disable criteria one-by-one to find which one excludes everyone. 3. Enrichment-dependent criteria (gear score, FC name, mount/minion/achievement counts) never match players the plugin hasn't enriched via Lodestone yet. 4. Encounter criteria need at least one logged shared territory — characters you've only briefly seen without entering an instance together won't match "Encountered in: Raids".</value></data>
